      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get the \"official\" explanation, but air traffic control has to follow logic too, right? if they are following certain waypoints that just happen to trace a grid, they’d still call it \"standard procedure.\" it's not like they'd admit to it. look at the flight corridors over the northeast corridor or london. if you pull up some recent flight logs for heavy international carriers, can you see if there's more overlap in specific sectors than what you'd expect for just one-way traffic? i want to see if there are repetitive \"loops\" that don't make sense for normal navigation.",
